The article is a transcript of a conversation between Vice President Kamala Harris and small business owners at Fibre Space, a boutique yarn shop in Alexandria, Virginia. The owners discuss their experiences during the COVID-19 pandemic and the challenges they faced in pivoting their business online. They highlight the importance of community and the impact of the pandemic on their staff and families. The Vice President acknowledges the difficulties faced by small businesses and emphasizes the need for support, including funding and vaccinations, to help them recover. The conversation also touches on issues such as childcare, women-owned businesses, and the role of small businesses in the community.